text:
dear rani mukherjee,

take off your yellow tinted glasses (literally), step down from your pedestal of power, move away from your privilege & then talk about the #metoo movement that has shaken the core of the power structure in our country, of the world.

your comments during the actresses round table discussion were not only disappointing, but extremely insulting to women everywhere. your take on sexual misconduct is why the world is not able to move beyond blaming women for anything and everything - including even the sexual assault that happens with them.

you're telling women to draw the line & kick men in the nuts, when they are being abused - do you even realize how impossible that is, in most situations? can a 6-month-old baby, an 18-month-old toddler or a 4-year-old kick her assailant?

don't tell girls to learn self defence to keep themselves safe from sexual predators - you are putting the onus on them to keep themselves safe, thereby making them think that it is their failure if they are unable to do so. is this the message you want to give the next-gen kids?

why should all the accountability be with the women? why not instead teach & preach the idea of looking at women with respect? why not tell all the privileged & entitled men out there to stop looking at the female gender as just breasts & vaginas?

your statements sadly prove that we are still stuck in a world, where the onus is still on the women to protect themselves, no matter what their age. isn't it time we started thinking of ways to change mentalities, mindsets & thoughts to create a world in which girls and boys are safe, and no girl ever has to think that her safety is her responsibility & hers alone!

thankfully deepika, alia & anushka spoke sense. but you, not so much. not at all, in fact. you had a powerful platform, you chose to not only make derogatory comments that destroyed the courage & strength shown by so many women when they revealed their stories & those who supported them.

sad. just so sad.

#metoo #metooindia #nizamimom #nizamimomtalks #hyderabadmom #roundtable #ranimukherjee #hyderabadinsta #momblogger #socialissues #socialactivist #notjustaprettyface #mommyblogger

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
mgtow 101: life insurance

i often here the typical pro black talk about businesses and land to generate wealth. this is true but many blacks don't have the type of business mind nor financial freedom to do these things. one thing we do have is a little cash that we spend monthly. we spend on clothes, liquor, games, jordans, weed and weave. might as well set aside something to change your kids lives. the best way to transfer wealth to your kids and family is through life insurance.

you can take out a million dollar life insurance for about 100-400 a month. assuming you paying the highest price that's about $12 dollars a day 80 dollars a week. every person on my page over 30 has 100 a month to spare. here are reasons why life insurance is better option.

1. tax efficiency 
life insurance is an¬†investment alternative¬†that offers you a solution to the tax headache created by many other wealth transfer vehicles. the proceeds from life insurance are free of income tax, so if your death benefit is $5 million, your heirs will receive the full $5 million.

2. guarantees

if you invested $1 million in a broad stock portfolio during the early 90s, you earned great returns for most of the decade. however, when the yea

market investing is exciting but loaded with risk. your only confidence that you will make money is looking at historical results, which are full of volatility. some people remain uncomfortable with the possibility of¬†losing half their moneywhen a recession hits, a market bubble bursts, or any number of other risks happen. 
if you pay your premiums and the insurer stays in business, you won‚Äôt have to worry about losing your money.

3. leverage

let‚Äôs say a $2 million policy on a healthy 65-year-old male costs $50,000 per year. upon making that first premium payment, that policyholder‚Äôs heirs are guaranteed to receive the full $2 million tax free, even if he dies in year one.

let‚Äôs say he lives to 85, which is very close to life expectancy, he would still have paid $1 million to receive $2 million ‚Äî a 100% return that boils down to 5% tax free per year. this is an example of the leverage offered by life insurance.

market investing is exciting but loaded with risk. your only confidence that you will make money is looking at historical results, which are full of volatility. some people remain uncomfortable with the possibility of¬†losing half their moneywhen a recession hits, a market bubble bursts, or any number of other risks happen. 
if you pay your premiums and the insurer stays in business, you won‚Äôt have to worry about losing your money.

text: predators are the craftiest of liars and manipulators. in fact, with each victim, they are able to  perfect their skills more and more. one tactic of choice is to introduce shaming and blaming as part of the lies and manipulation. for instance, one survivor mentioned how he told her "no one else is going to love you like i do". this was an outright lie. to compound the lie, he added manipulation via shaming and blaming, which caused her to question leaving him because she feared what others, family included, would say about her once she returned home. keep in mind, these girls had been isolated from family and friends for extended periods of time and many had gone in spite of what their parent(s) said, which means they already felt they had disobeyed or disrespected their family. so the lies and manipulation makes them feel they can't go back home, or home is no longer a safe place that will welcome them back with open arms. this is why it is imperative that when we teach our children about predatory behavior, we instill in them that no matter what someone tells them, they will always be believed and even if they disobey you or break the rules, they can always come home and you will love them. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #family @officialmuterkelly

text:
the girl who lost her star

my heart broke as i wrote.

in her father‚Äôs eyes she found delight
she lived to make him proud
to catch his gaze led to a plight
the moment he couldn‚Äôt be found
she was his girl, he was her star
but suddenly everything changed
a vicious call heard in a car
the poor child looked deranged
‚Äúthe precious man you hold so dear
has now been placed in jail‚Äù
dissolved into a pool of tears
and hopelessness prevailed
now in her teens and lost it seems
no value for her life
no schools, no baths or brushing teeth
her days are filled with strife
her father writhes in pain so deep
he says it‚Äôs all his fault
for promises he could not keep
can‚Äôt love her from a vault
she has no love for anyone 
not even for herself
save for a boy who‚Äôs less than scum
who makes her feel bereft
days are consumed with stalking him
it really breaks my heart
her tiny eyes are now so dim
e‚Äôer since she lost her star

text:
with the #metoo movement, we're in the era of calling people on their shit. here's my contribution..these are screenshots of messages i've received from my ex some time ago. the man that seemed to be the most enamored by me, was the biggest monster i've ever met.

#rkelly is the amplified model of what abuse looks like, but the color of a toxic relationship comes in many shades. so much so, that the simple solution of just leaving isn't as simple as it seems. and when you do walk away, there are psychological stains that come with it. this effect isn't just real for young girls, it's also real for grown, respected women who have their life together. 
i ask that you go through the images of messages and read over my personal list of warning signs.then share this message with a woman that you love and feel free to add to the list of warning signs.

bottom line..if you've been lucky to never experience abuse in your childhood, you don't easily recognize it until it's too late. you don't even know how to express what's happening to ask for help. you mistake it for the relationship going sour. but i have the tombstones of friends to back up my testimony and i'd rather speak my truth, than to add to that body of evidence. 
with all the friends that i have, i can count on 2 fingers, the number of people that helped me get away, 3 fingers of people who listened in support, but more fingers than i have to count, of people who watched and did nothing, defended him or added to the chaos-even blaming me. just like the reactions that have been seen in the case of the r. kelly situation. 
i hope that #rkelly gets the help that he needs, but wearing shackles while doing so. there's a difference between having a fetish and having a fetish that destroys the spirit of others. üé∂the remix to ignition should put your ass in prisonüé∂

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
{bubbles < $ therapy}
let‚Äôs talk about being apologetic, fickle, and silent in our intent and actions as women. why are we constantly apologizing for existing? how many times in a day do you apologize?
i was raised by a single mother and on a few occasions we were homeless. we stayed on people‚Äôs floors or couches and each time we would wake up fairly early and make the space we slept in look as if we had never been there. i learned eventually to be silent in spaces. i rarely spoke up with my thoughts and feelings. i let many things slide and in any relationship i hardly ever said out loud if something bothered me. i was extremely passive and as a result i‚Äôve had nearly 30 years of some pretty shitty relationships.
i‚Äôve learned the hard way to stand up for myself and to not be silent as a woman and as a human being. it has not been mentally or physically healthy for me.
after trump won the election in 2016 i decided i would no longer put up with ‚Äúbullshit‚Äù and i would no longer be silent about things that deserved to be spoken about. i also go to therapy once a week and am working hard on gaining confidence in every area of my life.
this post is my reminder to everyone out there, that it‚Äôs okay to not be silent, to be unapologetic, and to stand firm in decisions that are best for you or your loved ones. that‚Äôs okay. that‚Äôs healthy. ‚ù§Ô∏è

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
the words glow in the dark were written on my heart in the first few days of receiving divorce papers. ‚Ä¢

i had a flood of emotions, and had questions of ‚Äúwhy me.‚Äù ‚Äúwhy god didn‚Äôt save this.‚Äù ‚Ä¢

yet amongst my tears, sleepless nights, and prayers, the words reigned loud and clear in my heart, glow in the dark. ‚Ä¢
it truthfully made no sense.  i had no idea how i could even do that , ‚Äúglow‚Äù amongst my deepest sorry and hurt. 
like,  for real, what god!? ‚Ä¢

however, when i came to the end of myself, gods strength began to rise up, and quickly i found the light and glow, god was talking about. ‚Ä¢

the enemy would love to keep you down. keep you in the dark, feeling defeated, lonely, abandon, unloved, unworthy. ‚Ä¢

but if you refuse to believe these lies, you will find that god is just getting started! ‚Ä¢

you 100% can be the light amongst the darkness, as you seek jesus! ‚Ä¢

if the enemy can keep you stuck, far from god  and only looking at the darkness that surrounds you, then god can‚Äôt shine through you, and  finish your story. ‚Ä¢

and god wants you to radiate, no matter the dark place you may be in! ‚Ä¢
i don‚Äôt know what you are going through today, - divorce - separation - loneliness - abuse - broken relationships - financial struggles - abandonment - loss of a loved one ‚Ä¢

i don‚Äôt know. ‚Ä¢

but what i do know is, that you still have the ability to shine for jesus! ‚Ä¢

in fact, you can shine brighter and more beautiful than ever before. ‚Ä¢

light can shine brighter through a cracked vessel. the spaces allow for light to shine through in new ways and new designs.
‚Ä¢

fill yourself with hope in jesus and as you seek him, through the broken cracks of your heart, his light will seep through you. ‚Ä¢

text:
i've tried to keep quiet but from the memes to the spike in his music streams i can't.the "pied piper" lured children away from their parents  with music after they didn't pay him for luring the rats away from the village. get it?? the reason he was able to mock his victims by calling himself the "pied piper" is because he knows that this society has a female problem specifically a black female problem. we have been viewed as objects for centuries no matter the age. from doctors to parents people do not take the words of black girls/women seriously. we are so quick to protect these so called endangered "black male legends" that we overlook the fact that we have a misogyny problem within our community. .
.
#mythoughts #rkelly #imoverit #metoo #timesup #muterkelly #listentovictims

text:
one of my cousins mentioned to watch the docuseries surviving r kelly. i was hesitant knowing what could arise but went ahead with my husband by my side. 
furious, unsettled, confused, so many negative emotions surfaced.

however, i admired the strength, bravery and courage these women displayed in breaking their silence. 
i am for no one to pass judgment on victims because until you experience it, you won‚Äôt understand what these victims go through.

after twisting and turning in bed for most of this morning my vision became clear for #2019. in breaking the silence: i‚Äôm a survivor of child molestation in my grade school age, early teen years and sexual assault in the workplace as a young adult.  this year i start my journey to healing, breaking these generational curses and help to bring awareness to protect our little girls from these pedophiles out here. 
#survivor #metoo #breakingthesilence #journeytohealing #yourvoiceispower #speakup #believevictims #protectourdaughters #endchildmolestation #endsexualabuse #powerdownthesepedophiles

text:
dear black women, 
you are worth more than the world can offer. 
you are powerful. 
you are worth everything you demand and ask for. 
you will not be silenced. & i see you. i love you and i am proud of you. 
_____________________________________________________
long read, but its worth it: i woke up at 7:30 am with a heavy heart and mind. this entire first 7 days of the new year has been reflection and asking god to provide discernment for every encounter i will face. making sure my true vision of where i plan to go aligns with gods purpose for my life. 
i want to forever use my platform as a voice to share my stories in order to inspire change, & thought provoking messages. i am beyond disgusted by the entire #survivingrkelly documentary. thankful for sharing but disgusted it happened and is still happening. 
my heart was beating so fast and tears rolled down my eyes knowing that this man is walking the streets, living his life, and these women have nothing but money & pain to cover a wound. i have so many questions? how, why, what?!? so many questions as tears rolled down my eyes and anger started to ponder. 
the bottom line is that there is culture in the fashion industry and entertainment industry that is sick. yes, not all people in each industry partake in this behavior but the fact that some do is the reason i created @marzenterprise to be a voice for women not spoken for. at age 13, i was raped by a man i didn‚Äôt know. i was paralyzed by fear and didn‚Äôt have a moment to conclude my way out of the situation. that situation changed my life deeper than i would ever know. i am learning to share this part with women. no matter the circumstances you can heal better, you can still love, you can still grow, and you will still bloom. 
let me reintroduce myself my name is jasmine c. green and that‚Äôs who and all i am. the ceo, and founder of marz management and consulting enterprise, where we eradicate the limitations placed on creatives of color by expanding knowledge on diversity, sexual harassment, as well as health and wellness in the fashion industry. i am a #survivor. do not be afraid, no man can hurt what god deemed as powerful.
#metoo

text:
i wanted to start the new year on a positive note. but there is so much stupidity in this world, and sometimes this stupidity needs to be shared for others to take note, and think before they speak.

@moixyann a french writer/director/presenter, not a man of extra ordinary beauty himself, thought it okay in the post #metoo era, to age shame women, by telling marie claire fr in an interview, that he would never be able to love a 50 year old woman, being 50 himself. that idea would never come to mind. to moix, 50 year old women are invisible. he finds the 25 year old female body extra ordinary, contrary to a 50 year old female body. when he's 60 he could. because then he would think of a 50 year old woman as young. 
dear mr @moixyann, 
we, almost 50 and 50+ women, could never love stupid men like you, who still think of women as a piece of meat in the year 2019. apparently you didn't notice that we're years and years beyond the stone age, and we therefore advise men like you, to get in touch with doc. brown who can send you back to the future. 
yours sincerely,

text:
if a friend or family member is in an abusive relationship, be aware that they may have a very different point of view than you. they may have heard the abuse was their fault and feel responsible. even if they know it is an abusive relationship, they may choose to stay in the relationship. as a loved one, try to be there for them because although they may not show it, they need you more than ever. one way you can help is to acknowledge that they are in a very difficult and scary situation. be supportive and listen. let them know that the abuse is not their fault. reassure them that they are not alone and that there is help and support out there. it may be difficult for them to talk about the abuse. let them know that you are available to help whenever they may need it. what they need most is someone who will believe and listen.

if you have other questions about what you can do to help or just need support for yourself call us anytime, day or night, at 1-844-be-safe-1.

text:
it's a mixed bag of gratitude when "justice" occurs where "justice" was never served to begin with. i don't understand how she was sentenced in this way but can only hope that the clemency of cyntoia brown will challenge current cases and prevent similar outcomes in the future. 
this is why #ibelieveher and #blacklivesmatter. this is why the #metoo
movement matters (which, btw, originated by @taranajaneen pre hashtag world as an advocacy for black women survivors of sexual assault and violence. check out her organization just be inc.). also to note, look up the stats on abuse and violence against women of color. if that doesn't get you to care about this, then maybe it's time to get your heart checked. 
there are so many systemic issues and failures where our system protects a majority (that often is family, friends, and supporters of the system makers) but majorly fails the minorities and the marginalized. this post isn't an answer, because the answers start with you and what you are doing to be the change in the world. this is just a little psa.

text:
orthorexia¬†is the term for a condition that includes symptoms of obsessive behavior in pursuit of a healthy diet. orthorexia sufferers often display signs and symptoms of anxiety disorders that frequently co-occur with¬†anorexia nervosa¬†or other¬†eating disorders.
a person with orthorexia will be obsessed with defining and maintaining the perfect diet, rather than an ideal weight. she will fixate on eating foods that give her a feeling of being pure and healthy. an orthorexic may avoid numerous foods, including those made with:
* artificial colors, flavors or preservatives
* pesticides or genetic modification
* fat, sugar or salt
* animal or dairy products
* other ingredients considered to be unhealthy
common behavior changes that may be signs of orthorexia may include:
* obsessive concern over the relationship between food choices and health concerns such as asthma, digestive problems, low mood, anxiety or allergies
* increasing avoidance of foods because of food allergies, without medical advice
* noticeable increase in consumption of supplements, herbal remedies or probiotics
* drastic reduction in opinions of acceptable food choices, such that the sufferer may eventually consume fewer than 10 foods
* irrational concern over food preparation techniques, especially washing of food or sterilization of utensils
words from @timberlineknolls website üíõ

text: i promised myself that this year i wouldn‚Äôt act as if i‚Äôm cnn. whilst i have great reason to be outraged at least twenty three hours of the day, i will say i‚Äôve noticed taking in every bit of negative news to be leaving me with headaches and waves of anxiety. but today a pop of paracetamol may be worth it. i haven‚Äôt watched the ‚Äòsurviving r.kelly‚Äô documentary. i didn‚Äôt need to. sexual assault is so ingrained in the lives of black women, it‚Äôs a wonder how it‚Äôs not being sold next to tampax. growing up, most all my friends if not for sure their mothers had very violent stories of rape or sexual assault almost always committed by a person considered family. if not rape then for sure all of us has some sexual tryst with a man that knew us before we traded milk for mojitos and should‚Äôve known better. during slavery, rape was widely used as a form of discipline. for both men and women. as the years have tumbled forth and some wounds begin to heal, it is clear that we have yet to shake this particular ball and chain. going through comment sections where i read women describing kelly‚Äôs victims as ‚Äòfast‚Äô or ‚Äòacting too grown‚Äô reminded me of how far we have to go and how important it is to remember that black girls especially are still the bottom of the pile. there is a reason why the founder of the #metoo movement is a black woman. it‚Äôs because when it comes to tales of sexual assault black women‚Äôs voices are the last to be heard. but there is hope. i just heard that #cyntoiabrown was granted clemency. found guilty of killing a man who she was forced to sleep with because she was being pimped out at the time. she was 16. sentenced to 51yrs to life, it was clear that the law didn‚Äôt see a young black girl who was sexually preyed upon but a threat. like i said, she was just granted full clemency. so perhaps today‚Äôs paracetamol should be prosecco. #blackgirlsmatter

so this is why we need your help in seeing if our new guide would have been useful when you felt like that or feels useful now? you do not need to be a therapist or psychologist but if you are, please help us too! we will keep comments open until saturday, 12 january. click on the link in our bio to add your feedback! irrespective of whether you help us make this better or not, we just want to say we see you. we hear you. we are with you. you matter. your feelings matter.

text: i know i‚Äôm okay, i just need to breathe. breathe past my anxiety, the tears whelping up in my eyes, and all the sadness. most of all, breathe through this completely unexplainable pain in my heart. why can‚Äôt i explain why i‚Äôm hurt? why can i be so sensitive at the smallest details. it is estimated that 1 out of 5 adults in the us experience some type of mental illness. that‚Äôs around 50 million people that struggle everyday just like you and me. and i believe those who suffer are the strongest souls of them all. those with mental disorders that pick themselves up each day and live their life with true happiness and fulfillment is strong. you are carrying extra weight that others may not and still push no matter the hurtles. how strong are those who are challenged by their own mind each day and still choose to carry on. i don‚Äôt like to look weak. i used to hold myself up everyday to hide the fact i felt broken. ashamed of my diagnosis and how others will view me. it took time for me to come to a place where i was okay with being exactly who i am. i took medication, went to therapy, stayed at a hospital. it did help going through all that but what made me love and understand myself was educating myself in my disabilities and learning how they affect me. every day is a challenge but nothing i cannot handle on my own. #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #anxietyrecovery #depression #metoo #overcomedepression #loveyourself

text:
new podcast episode - one of the best ones yet!! trigger warning:
men face different hurdles in the entrepreneurial world. because of today's political correct environment, a lot of times, it's not okay to talk about those hurdles.
this week, purdeep and nathan discuss:
- why it's okay to focus on male entrepreneurs
- the differences between men and women in the workplace
- why the balance of masculine and feminine roles is so important
- how the #metoo movement is actually harming women in the workplace
- what men need to know about the fears women have
- why women can get away with things that men can't
- why women should listen to this podcast
tune in, but be warned. this one is not for the easily offended.
